OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43609
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1774555873
OL,3,CLength of storm overflow spills longer
OL,4,Cin South West than rest of England
OL,6,FIn 2025, there were nearly 300,000
OL,7,Fincidents when untreated sewage
OL,8,Fspilled from England's network of
OL,9,Fstorm overflows ` which should only
OL,10,Ftake place in "exceptional
OL,11,Fcircumstances" to prevent sewers being
OL,12,Foverwhelmed in heavy rainfall and
OL,13,Fbacking up into homes.
OL,15,FIn the second year of full monitoring
OL,16,Fof the network, there were 291,492
OL,17,Fspills across England, down more than
OL,18,Fa third (35%) on 2024's 450,398
OL,19,Fpollution events, the figures showed.
OL,26,@rD@OOUsD@NO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,437,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43610
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F436A1774555873
OL,3,CLength of storm overflow spills longer
OL,4,Cin South West than rest of England
OL,6,FTotal spill duration nearly halved
OL,7,Ffrom 3.61 million hours of sewage
OL,8,Freleases in 2024 to 1.87 million hours
OL,9,Fin 2025.
OL,11,FThe Environment Agency said much of
OL,12,Fthe improvement was due to the
OL,13,Funusually dry conditions in 2025,
OL,14,Fwhich left swathes of England battling
OL,15,Fdrought for much of the year, compared
OL,16,Fwith a very wet 2024.
OL,18,FWater minister Emma Hardy said there
OL,19,Fwas "still an unacceptable amount of
OL,20,Fsewage entering our waterways".
OL,26,@{D@EOU|D@^O]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/10
